NAME

	mlterm-gtk3-fcitx

DESCRIPTION

	The mlterm original is on http://mlterm.sourceforge.net/ .
	I'm using mlterm on Fedora, and Fedora do not have a mlterm rpm.
	So, I'd like to build it.

INSTALL

	$ sudo dnf copr enable tom0/mlterm-gtk3-fcitx
	$ sudo dnf install mlterm-gtk3-fcitx

BUILD

	If you'd like to build it. First, you should install RPM Development Tools group.
	
	And then,
	
		$ git clone git://github.com/jptomo/mlterm-gtk3-fcitx.git
		$ cd mlterm-gtk3-fcitx
		$ rpmbuild  mlterm-gtk3-fcitx.spec -bb
	
	or if you'd like to get SRPM, then,
	
		$ rpmbuild  mlterm-gtk3-fcitx.spec -bs

SEE ALSO

	https://copr.fedoraproject.org/coprs/tom0/mlterm-gtk3-fcitx/]
